        </p>
        <div style="float: right;">
          <div class="teifigure" style="width: 300px;"><a href="<?php echo($_ARCHON->PublicInterface->ImagePath); ?>/hoffmann-900w.jpg"><img src="<?php echo($_ARCHON->PublicInterface->ImagePath); ?>/hoffmann-300w.jpg" width="300" height="200" alt="Dr. Roald Hoffmann receiving the 2012 Pauling Legacy Award from OSU Libraries and Press Director Faye Chadwell and Linus Pauling, Jr." title="Dr. Roald Hoffmann receiving the 2012 Pauling Legacy Award from OSU Libraries and Press Director Faye Chadwell and Linus Pauling, Jr." /></a><br /><span class="caption-head">Dr. Roald Hoffmann receiving the 2012 Pauling Legacy Award from OSU Libraries and
                           Press Director Faye Chadwell and Linus Pauling, Jr.</span><br /><span class="caption-desc">(Click to enlarge)</span></div><br style="clear: both;" /></div>
        <p>The Pauling Legacy Award is just one of many ways in which Linus Pauling's life and
          work are celebrated at Oregon State University.  The <a href="http://scarc.library.oregonstate.edu/coll/pauling/index.html">Ava Helen and Linus Pauling Papers</a> form the cornerstone of the extensive history of science and technology holdings
          in the <a href="http://library.oregonstate.edu/">OSU Libraries</a><a href="http://scarc.library.oregonstate.edu/index.html">Special Collections &amp; Archives Research Center</a>.  The <a href="http://lpi.oregonstate.edu/">Linus Pauling Institute</a>, also located on the OSU campus, likewise continues to conduct groundbreaking research
          on diet and optimum health.  Two <a href="http://campaignforosu.org/howtogive/namingopportunities/endowedpositions/thelinuspaulingchairinchemicalengineering/">endowed</a><a href="http://campaignforosu.org/howtogive/namingopportunities/endowedpositions/theavahelenpaulingchair/">chairs</a> in the Pauling name have been placed within the OSU faculty and the annual <a href="http://oregonstate.edu/cla/pauling-memorial-lectures/pauling-memorial-lectures-world-peace">Ava Helen and Linus Pauling Memorial Lecture for World Peace</a> has been sponsored by the OSU College of Liberal Arts since 1982.
        </p>
